{"iteration":13,"action":{"reasoning":"Observation: The best test balanced_accuracy is 0.5528 from a 3-backbone (DINOv2+ResNet50+CLIP) concatenation with globally-trained balanced LR (C=1.0). Intercept tuning in iter 12 did not improve test performance. The predict.py in workspace is truncated/broken and must be rewritten before any further evals. Analysis: Since the held-out test domain (L100) differs drastically from source domains, a globally-trained classifier may overfit to spurious correlations present across all source domains. Training separate classifiers per source camera location and averaging their predictions at test time is a classic domain generalization technique: it reduces reliance on any single domain's background/lighting artifacts. Because features are already extracted, training 3 domain-specific LRs is very fast (~1 min). Decision: 1) Rewrite predict.py from scratch to robustly detect feature dimensions from any sklearn checkpoint and support ensemble lists. 2) Train a domain-specific ensemble of 3 balanced LRs (one per source domain) on the concatenated 3-backbone features. 3) Submit eval for the domain ensemble immediately.","command":"python train_domain_ensemble.py","submit_eval":{"checkpoint_path":"checkpoints/domain_ensemble.pkl","predict_script":"predict.py"},"done":false,"files_written":["predict.py","train_domain_ensemble.py"]},"command_output":{"exit_code":0,"timed_out":false,"elapsed_seconds":483.98732328414917,"stdout":"Loading 3-backbone features...\nTraining domain 0 classifier on 7810 samples...\n  Domain 0 train bal_acc: 0.8954\nTraining domain 1 classifier on 3212 samples...\n  Domain 1 train bal_acc: 0.8668\nTraining domain 2 classifier on 4892 samples...\n  Domain 2 train bal_acc: 0.8661\nDomain ensemble val balanced accuracy: 0.5932\nSaved checkpoints/domain_ensemble.pkl\n","stderr":""},"eval_result":{"metrics":{"balanced_accuracy":0.5606,"accuracy":0.6706,"macro_f1":0.399,"acc_bird":0.7407,"acc_bobcat":0.6842,"acc_cat":0.2